# VicaWellness - Cursor Rules

## Project Overview
This is a Next.js 14 web application for VicaWellness, a wellness and health platform built with TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, and modern React patterns.

## Tech Stack
- **Framework**: Next.js 14 with App Router
- **Language**: TypeScript
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS
- **Icons**: Lucide React
- **State Management**: React Context + useState/useReducer
- **Forms**: React Hook Form (when needed)
- **HTTP Client**: Fetch API (native)

## Code Style & Standards

### TypeScript
- Use strict TypeScript configuration
- Define proper interfaces and types for all data structures
- Use type assertions sparingly and with proper type guards
- Prefer interfaces over types for object shapes
- Use generic types when appropriate

### React & Next.js
- Use functional components with hooks
- Implement proper error boundaries
- Use Next.js App Router patterns
- Implement proper SEO with metadata
- Use Server Components by default, Client Components when needed
- Follow React best practices for performance

### Styling
- Use Tailwind CSS utility classes
- Create reusable component variants with clsx/tailwind-merge
- Follow mobile-first responsive design
- Use CSS custom properties for dynamic values
- Maintain consistent spacing and typography scales

### File Organization
```
src/
├── app/                 # Next.js App Router pages
├── components/          # Reusable UI components
│   ├── ui/             # Basic UI components
│   ├── forms/          # Form components
│   └── layout/         # Layout components
├── lib/                # Utility functions and configurations
├── hooks/              # Custom React hooks
├── context/            # React Context providers
├── types/              # TypeScript type definitions
├── utils/              # Helper functions
└── styles/             # Global styles and CSS
```

### Component Guidelines
- Use PascalCase for component names
- Export components as default exports
- Use proper prop interfaces
- Implement proper accessibility (ARIA labels, semantic HTML)
- Use proper loading and error states
- Follow single responsibility principle

### API & Data Fetching
- Use Next.js API routes for backend functionality
- Implement proper error handling for API calls
- Use proper HTTP status codes
- Implement data validation with TypeScript
- Use proper loading states and error boundaries

### Performance
- Implement proper image optimization with Next.js Image
- Use dynamic imports for code splitting
- Implement proper caching strategies
- Optimize bundle size
- Use proper memoization when needed

### Security
- Validate all user inputs
- Implement proper authentication and authorization
- Use environment variables for sensitive data
- Follow OWASP security guidelines
- Implement proper CORS policies

### Testing
- Write unit tests for utility functions
- Write integration tests for API routes
- Write component tests for critical UI components
- Use proper test data and mocking

